## Extracting the data from the h5py file

with h5py.File(filename, "r") as f:
    key0 = list(f.keys())[0]
    key1 = list(f.keys())[1]
    key2 = list(f.keys())[2]
    key3 = list(f.keys())[3]
    key4 = list(f.keys())[4]
    key5 = list(f.keys())[5]
    
    # Get the data
    X_test = np.array(list(f[key0]))
    X_train = np.array(list(f[key1]))
    X_val = np.array(list(f[key2]))
    y_test = np.array(list(f[key3]))
    y_train = np.array(list(f[key4]))
    y_val = np.array(list(f[key5]))

In [19]:
def plots(history):
    df = pd.DataFrame(history.history)
    fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1,2, figsize = (15,5))
    ax1.plot(np.array(df.index), df.loss , '-b', label='Training Loss')
    ax1.plot(np.array(df.index), df.val_loss, '--r', label='Validation Loss')
    ax2.plot(np.array(df.index), df.accuracy , '-b', label='Training Accuracy')
    ax2.plot(np.array(df.index), df.val_accuracy, '--r', label='Validation Accuracy')

    leg1 = ax1.legend();
    leg2 = ax2.legend();

## creating the 7th model

model7 =  Sequential()
model7.add(Dense(256, input_shape = (1024,), activation = 'relu'))

model7.compile(loss = 'categorical_crossentropy', optimizer = adam, metrics = ['accuracy'])

## fitting the model

## creating the 8th model

model8 =  Sequential()
model8.add(Dense(256, input_shape = (1024,), activation = 'elu'))
model8.add(Dense(256, activation = 'elu'))
model8.add(Dense(10, activation = 'softmax'))

## optimizer

adam = optimizers.Adam(lr = 1e-3, decay = 1e-5) ## optimizer ==Adam . 
## Reduced the learning rate to 10^(-4) since for higher learning rates the training did not happen at all. Also increased the decay

## compiling the model

model8.compile(loss = 'categorical_crossentropy', optimizer = adam, metrics = ['accuracy'])

## fitting the model

history8 = model8.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs = 100, batch_size = 1000, verbose = 1, validation_data= (X_val,y_val)) ## Training for 100 epochs

## creating the 10th model

model10 =  Sequential()
model10.add(Dense(512, input_shape = (1024,), activation = 'elu'))
model10.add(Dense(512, activation = 'elu'))
model10.add(Dense(512, activation = 'elu')) ## Adding another dense layer
model10.add(Dense(10, activation = 'softmax'))

## optimizer

adam = optimizers.Adam(lr = 1e-3, decay = 1e-5) ## optimizer ==Adam . 
## Reduced the learning rate to 10^(-4) since for higher learning rates the training did not happen at all. Also increased the decay

## compiling the model

model10.compile(loss = 'categorical_crossentropy', optimizer = adam, metrics = ['accuracy'])

## fitting the model

history10 = model10.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs = 100, batch_size =1000, verbose = 1, validation_data= (X_val,y_val))

c = 0
d = 0
for k in [model1,model2,model3,model4,model5,model6,model7,model8,model9,model10]:
    d = d+1
    y_pred = k.predict(X_test)
    for i in range(len(y_test)):
        if y_pred[i].argmax() == y_test[i].argmax():
            c = c+1
    print(f"Accuracy of model{d} :{np.round(100*c/len(y_test),2)}%")
    c = 0
